Vice President Biden will be traveling to Saratoga County, NY, on July 9th to highlight the progress of the Recovery Act. He will be speaking at Shenendehowa High School and discussing how the act is building a 21st-century economy in Saratoga County and across the nation. Governor David A. Paterson and Congressman Scott Murphy will also be in attendance. Limited public tickets are available on a first-come, first-served basis, and any remaining tickets will be distributed on July 8th. The event is open to the press, but media must RSVP by July 8th. The event details, including location and press access times, are provided in the article.